The '''Hiironi irstat''' was the largest [[Tarasin]] community on [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]]. It was formed from twelve [[irstat]] that had all settled independently near [[Cloud Mountain]]. When Cloud Mountain revealed itself to be a volcano by erupting, the twelve irstat were decimated. The survivors banded together and moved further away from Cloud Mountain, forming the Hiironi irstat. Their name reflected this history&mdash;"Hiironi" in [[Tarasinese]] meant "different but together."<ref name="LFC">''[[Living Force Campaign Guide]]''</ref>

When [[Reidi Artom]] came to Cularin, she made contact with the Hiironi irstat, not realizing they had no power to speak for the Tarasin as a whole, though its size did mean it was a focal point for a number of tribes. Artom and her crew founded the town of [[Gadrin]] near the irstat.<ref name="LFC" />

At the time that the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]] joined the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]], the Irstat-Ket (or "chief") of the Hiironi was [[Cryalira]], and their spiritual leader was Mother [[Dariana]].<ref name="LFC" />

Around [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]], occasional trading caravans went from Gadrin to the irstadt, to provide the Tarasin with advanced technology in exchange for their craft. The traffic kept away local predators and eased the trip, although some Tarasins, such as [[Dariana]], firmly believed that the Cularin had no use for the offered goods.<ref name="TRW">{{LivingForce|Eye of the Sun: The Resistance Within}}</ref>

